pull_request.title: Add scan-build to travis
pull_request.body:
To help prevent other issues like #194 I decided to add the scan-build checks on travis.

Note: it is normal that that the travis won't pass here, since scan-build's problems aren't solved yet.

pull_request.title: Covscan defect fix
pull_request.body:
FALSE POSITIVE
-------------

CID 1411664 (#1-8 of 8): Untrusted pointer read (TAINTED_SCALAR)
src/kex_rlwe_bcns15/fft.c


Comments:
 False positive if SHA_INIT flag set.  It's always set.

CID 1458082:    (UNINIT)
/src/kex_ntru/ntru_crypto_sha256.c: 105 in ntru_crypto_sha256_digest()
/src/kex_ntru/ntru_crypto_sha256.c: 105 in ntru_crypto_sha256_digest()


Comments:
False positive if SHA_INIT flag set. It's always set.

CID 1458079:    (UNINIT)
/src/kex_ntru/ntru_crypto_sha1.c: 676 in ntru_crypto_sha1_digest()
/src/kex_ntru/ntru_crypto_sha1.c: 676 in ntru_crypto_sha1_digest()


CID 1411663 (#1 of 1): Resource leak (RESOURCE_LEAK)
/src/crypto/rand/rand.c

CID 1458078 (#1 of 1): Out-of-bounds access (ARRAY_VS_SINGLETON)
src/kex_sidh_cln16/ec_isogeny.c in oqs_sidh_cln16_phn15()

CID 1458075 (#1 of 1): Out-of-bounds access (ARRAY_VS_SINGLETON)
src/kex_sidh_cln16/ec_isogeny.c


CID 1458083 (#1 of 1): Double free (USE_AFTER_FREE)
src/kex_sidh_cln16/kex_sidh_cln16.c in OQS_KEX_sidh_cln16_alice_0()

CID 1458085 (#1 of 1): Double free (USE_AFTER_FREE)
src/kex_sidh_cln16/kex_sidh_cln16.c in OQS_KEX_sidh_cln16_bob()


Comments:
Can be a problem if the while loop just above is not entered.

CID 1458084 (#1 of 1): Division or modulo by zero (DIVIDE_BY_ZERO)
src/kex_sidh_cln16/fpx.c in oqs_sidh_cln16_inv_mod_orderA()


CID 1411660 (#7-9 of 9): Division or modulo by float zero (DIVIDE_BY_ZERO)
src/kec/test_kex.c in kex_bench_wrapper

CID 1458081 (#1 of 1): Bad bit shift operation (BAD_SHIFT)
src/kex_sidh_cln16/ec_isogeny.c in oqs_sidh_cln16_phn84()
	

CID 1411659 (#1 of 1): Bad bit shift operation (BAD_SHIFT)
src/kex_rlwe_bcns15/fft.c in nussbaumer_fft() 


FIXED
-----

CID 1458086:  Integer handling issues  (SIGN_EXTENSION)
src/kex_ntru/ntru_crypto_ntru_encrypt.c: 890 in ntru_crypto_ntru_encrypt_keygen()

CID 1458073:  Integer handling issues  (SIGN_EXTENSION)
src/kex_ntru/ntru_crypto_ntru_encrypt.c: 890 in ntru_crypto_ntru_encrypt_keygen()


If cdf_table_len is 0 then there will be a problem:

CID 1411665 (#1 of 1): Uninitialized scalar variable (UNINIT)
src/kex_lwe_frodo/lwe_noise.c


CID 1458074 (#1 of 1): Resource leak (RESOURCE_LEAK)
src/kex_sidh_cln16/kex_sidh_cln16.c

Unclear about the semantics
---------------------------

CID 1458076 (#1 of 1): Out-of-bounds read (OVERRUN)
src/kex_ntru/ntru_crypto_sha2.c

CID 1458072 (#1 of 1): Out-of-bounds read (OVERRUN)
src/kex_ntru/ntru_crypto_sha1.c

CID 1411662 (#1 of 1): Out-of-bounds read (OVERRUN)
src/crypto/rand_urandom_chacha20/rand_urandom_chacha20.c

CID 1411661 (#1 of 1): Out-of-bounds read (OVERRUN)
src/crypto/rand_urandom_aesctr/rand_urandom_aesctr.c
